Business Brief -- Sterling Optical Corp.:
   Judge Approves Asset Sale
   To Owners of Cohen Chain
The Cohen brothers would pay $7.5 million in cash and $7.5
million in a five-year note. The spokeswoman said Sterling
still holds some real estate, which will be sold if the
company chooses not to reorganize. She said unsecured
creditors aren't expected to be repaid fully, but she didn't
elaborate.
   Cohen Fashion Optical is based in Hewlett, N.Y. Sterling
said the acquired optical business will be operated
separately from Cohen Fashion Optical.